The [Las Vegas Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip) is less a mere stretch of asphalt and more a monument to human ambition, or perhaps, desperation. It's a segment of [Las Vegas Boulevard](/Las_Vegas_Boulevard) within [Clark County, Nevada](/Clark_County,_Nevada), universally recognized for its unparalleled density of [resort hotels](/Resort_hotel) and [casinos](/Casino). When one speaks of "Vegas," more often than not, they're referring to this legendary, glittering ribbon of excess, even if the actual [Las Vegas](/Las_Vegas) city limits are just north of it. For those who find such distinctions tedious, "Vegas Strip" and "The Strip" lead directly here, while those seeking further nuances of the term can consult [The Strip (disambiguation)](/The_Strip_(disambiguation)).

Visually, the [Las Vegas Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip) is a kaleidoscope of architectural statements, each vying for attention. Images often capture its sprawling grandeur, from the vibrant pulse of [Las Vegas Boulevard](/Las_Vegas_Boulevard) itself to the distinct profiles of titans like the [MGM Grand Las Vegas](/MGM_Grand_Las_Vegas), the whimsical skyline of [New York-New York](/New_York-New_York_Hotel_and_Casino), the opulent facade of [The Venetian Las Vegas](/The_Venetian_Las_Vegas), the timeless Romanesque grandeur of [Caesars Palace](/Caesars_Palace), the conjoined spectacle of [Horseshoe Las Vegas](/Horseshoe_Las_Vegas) and [Paris Las Vegas](/Paris_Las_Vegas), and the iconic elegance of the [Bellagio](/Bellagio_(resort)). An interactive map only hints at the sheer scale of this urban marvel.

This iconic thoroughfare, approximately 4.2 miles (6.8 kilometers) in length, [1] is bookended by [Russell Road](/Russell_Road_(Las_Vegas)) to the south and [Sahara Avenue](/Sahara_Avenue) to the north. Geographically, it exists primarily within the [unincorporated towns](/Unincorporated_towns_in_Nevada) of [Paradise](/Paradise,_Nevada) and [Winchester](/Winchester,_Nevada), neatly sidestepping the actual municipal jurisdiction of [Las Vegas](/Las_Vegas) proper. A rather cunning move, if you ask me, allowing it to cultivate its own distinct identity, untethered from city politics. The coordinates 36°07′12″N 115°10′21″W mark its glittering heart.

Within this relatively compact expanse reside many of the globe's most colossal hotel casino and [resort](/Resort) properties. The sheer ambition of its offerings—spanning extravagant hotels, bustling [casinos](/Casino), world-class restaurants, towering residential high-rises, and an endless parade of entertainment—has cemented the [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip)'s status as an unparalleled and globally recognized tourist magnet. It is, without hyperbole, a primary engine driving the entire [Las Vegas](/Las_Vegas) economy. [2] So significant is this stretch that a substantial portion has been honored with the designation of an [All-American Road](/National_Scenic_Byway). [3] Furthermore, both the northern and southern segments of the [Las Vegas Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip) are proudly classified as [Nevada Scenic Byways](/List_of_Nevada_Scenic_Byways) and, indeed, part of the broader [National Scenic Byways](/National_Scenic_Byway) system, [4] a testament to its unique cultural and visual significance.

## Boundaries

One might imagine the boundaries of such a prominent landmark would be straightforward, but like many things in [Las Vegas](/Las_Vegas), there's a certain delightful ambiguity.

Historically, the earliest [casinos](/Casino) that chose to operate outside the burgeoning core of [Downtown Las Vegas](/Downtown_Las_Vegas) along [Fremont Street](/Fremont_Street) did so on [Las Vegas Boulevard](/Las_Vegas_Boulevard) itself, intentionally placing themselves beyond the city's reach. [5] [6] This strategic distancing set the stage for the [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip)'s unique jurisdictional status. A definitive, if somewhat arbitrary, marker of its fame arrived in 1959 with the erection of the iconic [Welcome to Fabulous Las Vegas sign](/Welcome_to_Fabulous_Las_Vegas_sign). [7] This beacon of kitsch and promise was deliberately placed 4.5 miles (7.2 kilometers) south of the then-city limits. Today, the sign resides in the median just south of [Russell Road](/Russell_Road_(Las_Vegas)), a point approximately 4.2 miles (6.8 kilometers) from [The Sahara](/Sahara_Las_Vegas) and roughly 0.4 miles (0.64 kilometers) south of the southernmost entrance to [Mandalay Bay](/Mandalay_Bay), which currently stands as the [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip)'s southernmost major casino. [8] [9]

In its most stringent definition, "the [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip)" refers exclusively to the segment of [Las Vegas Boulevard](/Las_Vegas_Boulevard) that falls roughly between [Sahara Avenue](/Sahara_Avenue) and that venerable "Welcome to Fabulous Las Vegas" sign. [10] [11] However, [Clark County](/Clark_County,_Nevada), ever practical, employs the broader term "Resort Corridor" to encompass the entire stretch of [Las Vegas Boulevard](/Las_Vegas_Boulevard) between the [215 Beltway](/Interstate_215_(Nevada)) and [Sahara Avenue](/Sahara_Avenue), along with its surrounding areas. [12] This suggests a concession to the sprawling nature of modern development.

From [Clark County](/Clark_County,_Nevada)'s perspective, [The Sahara](/Sahara_Las_Vegas) serves as the definitive northern boundary of the [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip). [10] Yet, many travel guides, perhaps swayed by the gravitational pull of sheer verticality, charitably extend this northern limit to include [The Strat](/Stratosphere_Las_Vegas), positioned a mere 0.4 miles (0.64 kilometers) further north. [13] [14] [15] Conversely, [Mandalay Bay](/Mandalay_Bay), situated just north of [Russell Road](/Russell_Road_(Las_Vegas)), is widely accepted as the southernmost resort truly belonging to the [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip). [13] The county officially designates the "Welcome to Fabulous Las Vegas" sign as the southern end, though it graciously acknowledges the popular contention that [Russell Road](/Russell_Road_(Las_Vegas)) might be a more accurate, or at least more pragmatic, southern terminus. [10] [16] Such debates are, I suppose, part of the charm of a place that thrives on illusion and flexible definitions.

