### Restaurants and dining

The [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip) has, over the years, evolved into a formidable culinary destination, a fact that might surprise those who still associate [Las Vegas](/Las_Vegas) solely with buffet lines. Its expanse is densely populated with an array of restaurants and [fine dining](/Fine_dining) establishments, the vast majority of which are conveniently nestled within the casino and resort properties. For a more exhaustive list, one might consult [Restaurants in the Las Vegas Valley § Las Vegas Strip](/Restaurants_in_the_Las_Vegas_Valley). In recent years, a veritable constellation of [celebrity chefs](/Celebrity_chef) has chosen the [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip) as the stage for their culinary empires, including luminaries such as [Wolfgang Puck](/Wolfgang_Puck), [Michael Mina](/Michael_Mina), the notoriously fiery [Gordon Ramsay](/Gordon_Ramsay), [72] the esteemed [Guy Savoy](/Guy_Savoy), [73] and the late, legendary [Joël Robuchon](/Jo%C3%ABl_Robuchon). [74] Their presence alone speaks volumes about the gastronomic ambitions of this particular stretch of desert.

### Shopping

If gambling isn't your vice, perhaps retail therapy will suffice. The [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip) offers an extensive, often bewildering, array of shopping experiences, from souvenir kitsch to haute couture.

• The Rainstorm Show at the Miracle Mile Shops at Planet Hollywood
• [The Forum Shops at Caesar's Palace](/The_Forum_Shops_at_Caesars)

Notable shopping destinations include:

*   [BLVD](/Blvd_(Las_Vegas)): A new three-story shopping center, adding to the ever-expanding retail footprint.
*   [Bonanza Gift Shop](/Bonanza_Gift_Shop): Proudly billing itself as the "World's Largest Gift Shop," this sprawling emporium offers over 40,000 square feet (3,700 m²) of retail space, a monument to souvenir excess.
*   [Fashion Show Mall](/Fashion_Show_Mall): Conveniently situated adjacent to [Treasure Island](/Treasure_Island_Hotel_and_Casino) and directly opposite [Wynn Las Vegas](/Wynn_Las_Vegas), it offers a more traditional mall experience.
*   [Grand Canal Shoppes](/Grand_Canal_Shoppes): A luxury mall seamlessly integrated with [The Venetian](/The_Venetian_Las_Vegas) and [The Palazzo](/The_Palazzo) resorts. Its unique charm lies in its intricate canals, complete with gondolas and serenading gondoliers, offering a slice of Venice in the desert.
*   [The Linq Promenade](/The_Linq_Promenade): An open-air retail, dining, and entertainment district that began its soft opening in January 2014. Located between [The Linq](/The_Linq) and [Flamingo](/Flamingo_Las_Vegas) resorts, it serves as a vibrant pathway leading from a [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip)-side entrance directly to the base of the [High Roller](/High_Roller_(Ferris_wheel)).
*   [Miracle Mile Shops](/Miracle_Mile_Shops): An integral part of the [Planet Hollywood Resort and Casino](/Planet_Hollywood_Resort_and_Casino) complex, offering a diverse range of stores.
*   [The Forum Shops at Caesars](/The_Forum_Shops_at_Caesars): A premier luxury mall connected to [Caesars Palace](/Caesars_Palace), boasting more than 160 shops and 11 restaurants, all under a simulated sky.
*   [The Shops at Crystals](/The_Shops_at_Crystals): A high-fashion luxury mall nestled within [CityCenter](/CityCenter), catering to the most discerning of shoppers.
*   [Harmon Corner](/Harmon_Corner): A prominent three-story retail center located adjacent to [Planet Hollywood](/Planet_Hollywood_Las_Vegas), featuring a mix of shops and restaurants.
*   [Showcase Mall](/Showcase_Mall): Positioned next to the [MGM Grand Las Vegas](/MGM_Grand_Las_Vegas), this mall is hard to miss, thanks to its towering 100-foot [Coca-Cola](/Coca-Cola) bottle. [75]
*   The Park: A short, pedestrian-friendly east-west street situated between the [Park MGM](/Park_MGM) and [New York-New York Hotel & Casino](/New_York-New_York_Hotel_%26_Casino) resorts. Designed as a park-like boulevard, it's lined with retail shops and restaurants, culminating at the impressive [T-Mobile Arena](/T-Mobile_Arena). [76]
*   [The Shoppes at Mandalay Place](/Mandalay_Bay): A collection of shops and restaurants uniquely situated on a sky bridge connecting [Mandalay Bay](/Mandalay_Bay) and [Luxor](/Luxor_Las_Vegas). [77]

### Live sports

The [Las Vegas Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip) has increasingly become a major hub for professional sports, a development that might have seemed improbable just a few decades ago. [78] Venues on or in close proximity to the [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip) now host a variety of major league teams and events, solidifying its status as a sporting destination.

• The [MGM Grand Garden Arena](/MGM_Grand_Garden_Arena) hosting the boxing match of [Manny Pacquiao vs. Keith Thurman](/Manny_Pacquiao_vs._Keith_Thurman) on July 20, 2019

Current professional sports affiliations include:

*   [National Football League](/National_Football_League): The [Las Vegas Raiders](/Las_Vegas_Raiders) proudly call [Allegiant Stadium](/Allegiant_Stadium) their home.
*   [National Hockey League](/National_Hockey_League): The [Vegas Golden Knights](/Vegas_Golden_Knights) electrify crowds at [T-Mobile Arena](/T-Mobile_Arena).
*   [Mixed Martial Arts](/Mixed_Martial_Arts): The [Ultimate Fighting Championship](/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship) frequently stages its high-octane events at [T-Mobile Arena](/T-Mobile_Arena).
*   Boxing: The [MGM Grand Garden Arena](/MGM_Grand_Garden_Arena) remains a storied venue for major boxing matches.
*   [Women's National Basketball Association](/Women%27s_National_Basketball_Association): The [Las Vegas Aces](/Las_Vegas_Aces) showcase their talent at the [Michelob Ultra Arena](/Michelob_Ultra_Arena).

Beyond team sports, the [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip) also plays host to the high-octane spectacle of the [Las Vegas Grand Prix](/Las_Vegas_Grand_Prix), which joined the esteemed [Formula One World Championship](/Formula_One_World_Championship) calendar in [2023](/2023_Formula_One_World_Championship). [79] The future promises even more sporting grandeur with the impending [New Las Vegas Stadium](/New_Las_Vegas_Stadium), set to become the home of the [Oakland Athletics](/Oakland_Athletics) in 2028 when the team completes its relocation to the [Las Vegas Valley](/Las_Vegas_Valley). [80] The athletic ambitions don't stop there; in 2024, a proposal emerged for an NBA-ready arena on the [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip), integrated into the planned [LVXP](/All_Net_Resort_%26_Arena) resort development. [81] [82] It seems the [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip) is determined to conquer all forms of spectacle.

### Golf

Once upon a time, even the [Las Vegas Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip) had golf courses. The [Aladdin](/Aladdin_(hotel_and_casino)), for instance, boasted a nine-hole golf course in the 1960s, [83] a quaint notion now. However, as the value of land on the [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip) has skyrocketed over the decades, these resort-affiliated golf courses have progressively been sacrificed to make way for more lucrative building projects. [84] The [Tropicana Country Club](/Tropicana_Country_Club) closed its greens in 1990, [85] followed by the [Dunes](/Dunes_(hotel_and_casino)) golf course in the mid-1990s.

A notable exception to this trend involved [Steve Wynn](/Steve_Wynn), the visionary founder of the previously owned [Mirage Resorts](/Mirage_Resorts). He acquired the [Desert Inn](/Desert_Inn) and its accompanying golf course for his new enterprise, [Wynn Resorts](/Wynn_Resorts_Limited), subsequently redeveloping the course into the acclaimed Wynn Golf Club. This course, too, briefly closed in 2017 with plans for a new development, but those plans were ultimately canceled, leading to the course's renovation and triumphant re-opening in late 2019. [86] Just south of [Mandalay Bay](/Mandalay_Bay) and the main [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip), the Bali Hai Golf Club opened in 2000, offering a touch of tropical links. [87] In 2016, the popular [TopGolf](/TopGolf) driving range and entertainment complex opened near the [Strip](/Las_Vegas_Strip), catering to a more casual golfing crowd. [88]

